      },
      "date": "2021-06-18 22:42:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nStrange, the build is failing with:\nhttps://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/81466/arch=x86_64,build_type=server,distro=el7.7,ib_stack=inkernel/console\n\n 12:37:34 /usr/bin/install: will not overwrite just-created '/tmp/rpmbuild-lustre-jenkins-2uVM9fNB/BUILDROOT/lustre-2.14.52_15_g05e1899-1.x86_64/usr/share/man/man8/lnetctl.8' with 'lnetctl.8'\n12:37:34 /usr/bin/install: will not overwrite just-created '/tmp/rpmbuild-lustre-jenkins-2uVM9fNB/BUILDROOT/lustre-2.14.52_15_g05e1899-1.x86_64/usr/share/man/man8/lst.8' with 'lst.8'\n\nbut it isn't clear how this patch is causing the problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "2b7425574608f19416ccfa04e1ee04a931d73830",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2021-06-18 23:00:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(4 comments)\n\nIt looks like the same man pages are listed twice:\n\n 12:43:30  /usr/bin/install -c -m 644 lnetctl.8 lst.8 mount.lustre.8 mount.lustre_tgt.8 lctl.8 lctl-get_param.8 lctl-list_param.8 lctl-network.8 lctl-pcc.8 lctl-pool_add.8 lctl-pool_new.8 lctl-set_param.8 ldev.8 lhbadm.8 ll_decode_linkea.8 llobdstat.8 llog_reader.8 llsom_sync.8 llstat.8 lnetctl.8 lst.8 \n\nThis is due to duplication in MANFILES vs. SERVER_MANFILES, and just randomly hit by this patch because of how \"install\" is splitting the command-line arguments.  I think the common pages should be in MANFILES, and server-only pages should only be in SERVER_MANFILES.\n\nIt would be great to also take this opportunity to sort these lists to make it easier to compare them.\n\nThis should add:\n\n Fixes: 15305c3c3fe7 (\"LU-12214 build: fix build without lustre_utils\")\n\nsince that patched introduced the problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
